# Markdown defaults

Contract: [shared-docs-precedence](../shared/shared-docs-precedence.mdc), [shared-docs-toc](../shared/shared-docs-toc.mdc)

## When the rule applies

- Apply to authored Markdown and Markdown-shaped content in the workspace, including `.mdc` rule files.

## Behavior

**Universal.** Thin base rule for workspace Markdown.

**Precedence:** `shared-docs-precedence.mdc` is the sole source for rule order and tie-breakers.

**Path overrides:** Devblog and `doc/playbook/` contract stacks override this file for their matched paths when loaded. Invocation-gated workflow instructions also override this file only for the active invocation. Order and tie-breakers live only in `shared-docs-precedence.mdc`.

**Triggers:** `auto-docs-markdown`, `auto-markdown`, `markdown defaults`, `markdown-defaults`, `markdown base`, `rule router`

Formatting and voice behavior follow [style-guide](../../_core/style-guide.md). Personal-account voice follows `shared-docs-voice.mdc` for its glob-matched paths. TOC format and inclusion conditions are defined in `shared-docs-toc.mdc`.

### TOC behavior

TOC inclusion conditions are defined in `shared-docs-toc.mdc`. When a TOC is present or requested, format and anchors follow `shared-docs-toc.mdc`.

**Devblog.** When a project ships an always-on devblog rule for `**/devblog/**/*.md`, that rule governs weekly entry TOC placement and inclusion. Format and anchor rules defer to `shared-docs-toc.mdc`. Voice defers to `shared-docs-voice.mdc`.

## Examples

Example: For a generic `README.md` section with no higher-priority rule loaded, apply this file plus [style-guide](../../_core/style-guide.md); do not invent path-specific caps inside this base layer.

